                                         CAPE TOWN - A former employee at the Department of Home Affairs  has been arrested for issuing fraudulent permits. The Hawks’ Serious Anti-Corruption Unit has arrested a 34-year-old female for allegedly issuing fraudulent permits. During 2015, the suspect allegedly manipulated the department’s administration system. She issued permits to foreign nationals, asking a fee of just over R10 000 each permit. The Hawks Lloyd Ramovha said: “Comprehensive investigations resulted in the arrest of the suspect on November the 3rd. She has been warned to appear in Cape Town Regional Court on November the 13th to face charged related to corruption and fraud.”